<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="541">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[374,515,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 5, 6" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,191,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1749]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5, 6. Myanmar Trichoptera spp. 5A–5E, Lepidostoma pennicularium spec. nov., scale = 0.5 mm: 5A, genitalia, left lateral; 5B, genitalia, ventral; 5C, genitalia, dorsal; 5D, head, left lateral; 5E, right forewing venation, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637994" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637994/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="541">Figs 5A–5C</figureCitation>
). Dorsomesal process of segment IX absent, lateral processes long, apically rounded, sinuous in dorsal view, diverging apically; ventral processes acute. Inferior appendages each with first article long, slender, bearing elongate, subapical brush of hairs on ventral side, basodorsal process slender; second article slightly split at apex. Phallic apparatus with aedeagus strongly recurved near base, parameres asymmetrical, apical portions criss-crossed and curved in different directions.
</paragraph>
